               <msContents>
                  <summary>The first section of the text on this papyrus is concerned with an assessment of gold for defraying the expense of transporting military supplies by mule-train from the point of collection to the camps. The second section is devoted to the provision of vestis militaris.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Verso; Recto contains much battered remains of a column of writing which bears the title  apaitesimon ekphorion.</note>
                     <note type="related">-</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
